1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Join me as you explore the Media Library and ways to organize all your media.

2
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:09,040
You can add various types of media to your library, from photos, screenshots, audio,

3
00:00:11,440 --> 00:00:14,440
PDF documents, spreadsheets, PowerPoint presentations and more.

4
00:00:16,740 --> 00:00:19,740
If you have a lot of media in your library, it might start feeling a bit disorganized

5
00:00:20,480 --> 00:00:23,480
or intimidating to manage all your media.

6
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:26,360
You may be asking, isn't there a way to categorize your media?

7
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:30,400
Well the answer is yes, we are going to use a plugin to achieve this goal.

8
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:36,040
Let's make our way to Plugins and click on Add New.

9
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:41,880
I'm going to type "Media plugin organizer" in the search box and within a second or two

10
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
we will be able to choose from a variety of options.

11
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,600
I will be selecting an open source plugin called Media Library Organizer.

12
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:55,920
Media Library Organizer doesn't replace the look and feel of the Media Library, instead

13
00:00:57,960 --> 00:01:00,960
it will enhance the WordPress user interface, adding key features needed for mass organization

14
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:06,840
as well as searching and filtering of media.

15
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:10,680
There are many other plugins to choose from in the Plugin Directory, for example, number

16
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,880
one WordPress Real Media Library, number two FileBird or number three Wicked Folders.

17
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:23,680
Let's go ahead and install the Media Library Organizer plugin and always remember to click

18
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:29,760
Activate.

19
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:33,080
When I return to the Media Library, you will see we now have a new left sidebar called

20
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:38,280
Media Categories and you have three options to add, edit and delete.

21
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:44,480
Due to the fact that I haven't created any categories, I only have the option to add

22
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:48,760
new categories and subcategories.

23
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:51,400
I'm going to go ahead and create a new category and name it Traveling.

24
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:57,880
Then I will click on Bulk Select and choose the appropriate images.

25
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:06,360
And once I've done that, I'm going to drag and drop them to the new category.

26
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:11,840
The second category that I want to create is going to be called Nature and once I've

27
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:16,200
created the folder, I will once again click on Bulk Select and then choose all the relevant

28
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:22,400
images I want to add to this category.

29
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
And once I've finished selecting all the media, I will drag and drop them to their new category

30
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:32,720
called Nature.

31
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:36,640
The third category I want to create is going to be called Lifestyle.

32
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:42,040
Now I will click on the category to add subcategories.

33
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:45,760
I will right click on my mouse, select Add Child and name my subcategories.

34
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:51,600
The first one is going to be called Exercise and the second one, Recipes.

35
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Once I've done that, I will click on Bulk Select, choose the exercise images and drag

36
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:14,560
and drop them to their new category.

37
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:24,520
Lastly I want to create three more subcategories within Recipes.

38
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:28,320
The first category is going to be called Vegetarian, the second one Meat and the last one Breakfast.

39
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:41,680
Once I've created the subcategories, I will choose Bulk Select and drag and drop the

40
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:46,080
images to their respective categories.

41
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:48,840
So first breakfast, then my vegetarian options and then a meat dish.

42
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:01,080
And now you will see all the images in their categories.

43
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:07,760
The display of categories we see here is called tree view and is used for easy searching,

44
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:13,800
filtering and bulk categorization.

45
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:17,120
If you click on Unassigned, you will be able to view all the images or files that have

46
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:21,680
not yet been categorized.

47
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:26,200
If you right click on a category and decide to delete it, the images or files will merely

48
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:30,720
return to being unassigned.

49
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:34,640
As you have seen, using a media manager plugin can help you organize and feel more in control

50
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:40,320
of your site's media.

